message:
Excellent article, however I have one more question about chaining awaitables.

Consider the following example:

In the top-level method I don't want the awaiter to capture the current context. So I add ConfigureAwait(false) for the DoSomeTaskAsync task.

Should ConfigureAwait(false) be added in every sub method given that every method does'nt need the current context.

// "top-level" method.  
public void HandleSomething(...) {  
 var task = DoSomeTaskAsync(...);  
 ...  
 var result = await task.ConfigureAwait(false);  
 ...  
}

private async Task<tresult> DoSomeTaskAsync(...) {  
 var task = DoSomeInnerTaskAsync(...);  
 ...  
 return await task.ConfigureAwait(false) // Is ConfigureAwait(false) required?  
}

private async Task<tresult> DoSomeInnerTaskAsync(...) {  
 var task = SomeLib.DownloadString(...);  
 ...  
 return await task.ConfigureAwait(false) // Is ConfigureAwait(false) required?  
}

Many thanks,
